  {
   "annotation_marker": "c",
   "annotation_type": "footnote",
   "annotation_text": "LY2835219 should be administered every 12 hours on Days 1 through 28 of each cycle. Patients should not consume food beginning 1 hour before and ending hour after taking study drug. Fulvestrant 500 mg should be administered intramuscularly into the buttocks slowly (1 to 2 minutes per injection) as two 250-mg injections, one in each buttock; however, for patients with moderate hepatic impairment (defined as Child-Pugh Class B), including any patient who develops moderate hepatic impairment during study treatment, fulvestrant 250 mg should be administered intramuscularly into the buttock slowly (1 to 2 minutes) as one 250-mg injection.",
